tip.text: This non-descript hotel is in a prime location, and has nice rooms. Check ins done at Hotel Monaco, approx 3-5mins walk away.
If possible, avoid this place. Not worth visiting.
Pathetic servings, but I guess you get what you pay for. Euro11.90-13.90 for a three-course meal, with no cover charge. Waiters don't speak English well, hence the miscommunications, too.
The all-you-can-eat ribs comes only in half-rack portions + original BBQ sauce. Nonetheless, if you're a big eater, it's definitely worth going for. For 40 bucks+, you can have your fill of ribs!
Char siew is a slice of heaven. Password for it is "pun fei sao". Don't ask why. LOL
The service is bad, and they should feel bad. Food is alright though.
Had one of the best salted caramel macchiatos in my life. It was so good! :)
Service is alright. The interior is pretty cool, and there's a live band (which isn't that good but okay). Stuff here is a bit on the pricey side, though.
Curry mee is damn good here, and the siham is forever fresh one hahaha.
The pork patties are so juicy...just perfect :) Only problem is that the burger is too big to bite on (which is not really a problem anyway). Definitely the best dayummm pork burgers :)
The rojak had a sweet sauce and all the toppings of a mee rebus but had veggies (taugeh, cucumber, etc) underneath instead. Didn't like it as much as the ABC & mee rebus, which was really good.
Coffee was so-so. Strawberry shortcake wasn't quite a shortcake but still good I guess. The fruit tart is yummy, save for the base which was a bit hard. Nice interior, worth a visit! :)
Sloppy fries were good. The cupcakes were pretty great too (but they're tiny. Boo :p) Felt like the service was sub-par as they served someone else when I was clearly in line before them.
